p: \rWhat a lovely chap. I could barely keep myself from cheering!
\bOranos Town is my favourite place in the region.
\bIt doesn't have any of the special features the bigger cities have, but it's quaint, out of the way, and everybody here is so friendly.
\rMy husband and I moved to Oranos Town from Selene City just a while back and he can't stop talking about it.
\rI must say though, I agree. Selene City was super creepy!
\bHmm? Who are you? Why are you talking to me?
\bI'm so glad we have someone so clearly not evil as Zachary to help us.
\bI don't buy it. Everyone knows that vaccines cause Pokerus!
\bYou know, Zachary looks a lot like that cult l... or maybe not.
\bHonestly, it's hard to tell. Everyone in this region looks the same anyway.
\bHave I seen you before? On the news, maybe?
\bOh! You were the trainer who fought Xavier in their Gym!
\bWhat a great fight. I tried, myself... that Beedrill stopped me right in my tracks!
\rMan, Zachary is so brave. I'm so glad people like he and the Augur are around.
\bI can't quite place it. You're a kid. Never you mind.
\rThis line has been going on forEVER. The building must have been a storage for Lagging Tails or something.
\bI help take care of the gardens in the middle of the town. Aren't they pretty? I'm so proud!
\bMan, I love Zachary. He's so dreamy- and so helpful!
\bHe's so definitely not a cultist, it's wonderful!
\rI'm so glad you young folk are around. You're the future of this region, you know?
\bBack of the line, bucko! You can't butt in in front of me!
\bSome of the trainers around are brutal. I wish I started my adventure in Telnor Town...
\bIt's almost impossible to start your adventure here! The sheer level gap!
\rOne of my cousins is in the Elite Four. She's just graduated college and now she's decimating trainers left and right.
\bThis whole disease thing is pretty freaky. I'm glad we have someone like Zachary to help sort us out, y'know?
\rWe're all in line for these weird vaccination things.
\bOranos Town is such a pretty town.
\bI'm filming a documentary about the disease breakout.
\bZachary hired me a while back, he's been telling me what to shoot and what to publish.
\bMan, it's so nice not to have to stay organized myself! What a great guy.
\bI don't like it. Not one bit. We've had scares like this before and they never end well.
\bI just hope we don't have any people trying to take advantage of Torrennites again!
\bThank goodness we have a trustworthy person like Zachary to look up to.
\bThis whole business about the virus, I didn't like it at first and I don't like it now.
\bNow that it turns out Zachary was a cultist, I wonder what the vaccine was for.
\bWe used to have a leftover storage facility here, but Zachary's repurposed it.
\bNot sure what he's using it for... it's all very hush-hush.
\bHe dumped all the junk out. It's kind of a mess now.
\bIt's crazy to think that Zachary and Zenith were the same person.
\bIt's crazy to hear about all the stuff that goes on behind the scenes.
\rThere's a cool tower owned by Satellite Corps just east of here.
\rI heard they were having some weird electricity problems, but I'd love to work there one day.
\rElectrical engineering is a passion of mine! I could help!
\bI hear they're rebuilding the Battle Frontier here in Torren.
\bI can't wait! I've always wanted to try that out.
The statue seems to be a shrine to the Pokemon League.
Most of the words are scratched out...
\rMy mom says I can't go out and play with my Pokemon anymore...
\rHmph. I guess you could have this, then. I don't need it.
\rMy mom says I can't go out and play with my Pokemon anymore...
\rListen... I have this theory about Delta Species Pokemon.
\rThey almost always turn into "cool typings", like Dragon, Fire, Ice...
\rCome to think of it, I don't think I've ever seen a Grass-type or Normal-type Delta.
\rIf you can show me one, I'll give you a prize.
\rDo you have a Grass- or Normal-type Delta to show me?
\rWell, come back later if you find one.
\rI guess I was wrong. Thanks for showing me.
\rLet me think... oh, I know. A good TM will be your prize.
\rHopefully that TM can help you out. Thanks for your assistance.
\bI'll trade you my Gible for any Water-type!
\bWell, come back if you change your mind!

\bSo many people are lining up for this vaccine...
\bThank goodness Zachary is a good person. I shudder to think what a cultist could do with this kind of influence.
\bIt's scary to think he was a cultist. Thank god he was taken down, I shudder to think of what he could have done with that kind of power.
\rMy mom said she saw a Girafarig with a Mega Stone...
\rBut that's impossible. Girafarig can't Mega Evolve!
\bYou look like a fine, upstanding, young adult.
\bI heard there was a Hidden Grotto somewhere around here with Froakies in it.
\bThat's crazy! A Pokemon all the way from Kalos- I'd love that!
\bI finally got accepted into the Trainer School.
\bI can't wait to start learning about competitive battling in the fall!
\bMy favourite lesson is about how balanced and fair Mega Rayquaza is but how the competitive scene shouldn't let Meloetta in.
\bI agree! Could you imagine how dumb the meta would be if we let in Meloetta?
\bGood thing we're just sticking with our primal legendaries.
